  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The performance of an investigational immunochromatographic strip (ICS) test for the
      diagnosis of syphilis is compared with the Abbott Laboratories Determine ICS test. The study
      population consists of patients with and without syphilis presenting to sexually transmitted
      disease clinics in five cities in the United States. Specimens include finger-stick whole
      blood (investigational test only) and whole blood, plasma, and serum by venipuncture.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
